<br>
If you believe that everyone in your country has right to have a job, eat and live in a decent house, and free decent education, you can't rely mostly on charity to enforce those rights. You have to raise taxes until there is enough cash to guarantee that right for everyone (or change your mind about what rights citizens should have, lol). <br>
<br>
Citizens getting benefits from social policies are not 'beggars', they are getting what is due to them, no need to say 'please' or 'thanks' to a rich guy.<br>
<br>
Charity will be useful for some people in need, but will never be a guarantee of solving a problem. You may give for charity one year, maybe because you need to feel generous, then be greedy next year and give a few coppers. Charity is a 'temporary' fix, until the problem is really dealt with, never a way to solve the problem.<br>
<br>
So no, don't force them to give for charity, just tax their @$$ hard. Of course not too hard or the economy will be hurt, but as hard as you need to guarantee that there is enough cash to have decent social policies in your country. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=577826">Echtelion HeavyHand</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
