No where in our Constitution are these so called rights mentioned. As a matter of fact it looks more like socialism than any thing.<br>
<br>
In America you have many rights and privileges, along with rights and privileges come responsibilities. No where in the rights and privileges will you find the government responsible for your employment, food, housing and schooling. The fact that these are provided are social benefits not rights.<br>
<br>
In America you have the right to:<br>
Get legal employment to what ever level you can up to and including starting your own business.<br>
To buy as much food of what ever quality as you can afford.<br>
Buy a house and own property which for the most part is yours and you can pass on to your children (Issue here with the way taxes have made this difficult for poorer citizens).<br>
Get the finest medical treatment you can afford.<br>
Send your children to the finest schools you can afford.<br>
<br>
They are there if you want them but you have to work for them they are not just freebies because you exist. If the people wanted them to be &quot;Rights&quot; then we would need to amend the Constitution. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=coslinroguebarbarian>CoslinRogueBarbarian</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 329<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(4/21/03 11:21:56 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm62.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=345.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Being Rich?!?</span><hr size=1> Once again.. Siffo is very wise.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
